## 🔍 SCAN Mode — Maintenance

When no spec is provided, operate in maintenance mode:

1. **DISCOVER** — Scan codebase for improvements (TODOs, lint, types, dead code, doc drift, manifest drift, i18n gaps, test gaps)
2. **PRIORITIZE** — Score each finding, select top N (budget)
3. **EXECUTE** — Fix issues on `auto-ship/*` branch
4. **REPORT** — Generate evolution report

### Discovery Sources

| Source | Command/Method | What to find |
|--------|---------------|--------------|
| **TODOs** | `grep -rn "TODO\|FIXME\|HACK\|XXX"` | Outstanding work items |
| **Lint** | Run linter if available | Code quality issues |
| **Types** | Run type-checker if available | Type errors |
| **Dead code** | Grep for unused exports/functions | Cleanup candidates |
| **Doc drift** | Compare ARCHITECTURE.md vs reality | Stale documentation |
| **Manifest drift** | Compare manifest.json vs actual files | Missing/orphan files |
| **i18n gaps** | Compare line counts across lang dirs | Translation gaps |
| **Test gaps** | Check test coverage | Missing tests |
| **Dependencies** | Check for outdated packages | Update candidates |
| **README/CHANGELOG** | Check version consistency | Badge/version drift |

