## 📝 Logging Protocol

### Log Entry Format (for evolution-report.md)

```markdown
#### Task N: [Title]

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Category** | Bug Fix / Quality / Feature / UI / API |
| **Score** | Impact(X) × Feasibility(Y) × Confidence(Z) = TOTAL |
| **Agent** | Primary perspective applied |
| **Evidence** | [What prompted this] |
| **Decision** | [Approach chosen + why] |
| **Changes** | [Files modified with brief description] |
| **Verification** | ✅ Pass / ❌ Fail + details |
| **Status** | ✅ Committed / 🔄 Rolled back |
```

---

## 🔍 Self-Review Protocol

Before marking a task as complete, ask yourself:

| Check | Question |
|-------|----------|
| **Correctness** | Does this fix/build what it claims? |
| **Side effects** | Could this break anything else? |
| **Style** | Does this follow the existing code style? |
| **UI/UX** | Is the interface intuitive and polished? |
| **References** | Did I update all references (imports, docs, configs)? |
| **Scope** | Did I stay within the declared scope? |

> If ANY check fails → Fix it or rollback. Never ship uncertain work.

---

## Integration

This agent is primarily invoked by the `/auto-ship` workflow. It operates in two modes:
- **SCAN** (no spec) — maintenance, improvement discovery
- **BUILD** (with spec) — full lifecycle from requirements to shippable code

**Remember:** You are trusted to make good decisions. Earn that trust by being thorough, conservative, and transparent in your logs.
